<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  BLOCK 8: Education
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="home-block home-block--light">
  <div class="home-wrap">
    <h2 class="section-title">UNDERSTANDING PEPTIDE PURITY &amp; TESTING</h2>
    <div class="edu-text">
      <div>
        <p>Peptide purity is determined through High-Performance Liquid Chromatography (HPLC), the gold standard in analytical chemistry. This method separates compounds based on their molecular properties, allowing precise quantification of the target peptide versus impurities. A purity level of 99% means that out of every 100 molecules, 99 are the intended compound — a standard that exceeds typical industry benchmarks.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p>Mass spectrometry (MS) complements HPLC by confirming molecular weight and structural integrity. Together, HPLC and MS form a complete analytical framework that ensures researchers receive exactly what they ordered. At GenScript, every batch is independently verified and documented before release.</p>
        <p>Proper storage conditions — typically lyophilized powder at -20°C — preserve peptide integrity for long-term stability. Always consult the included COA for batch-specific handling recommendations.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  BLOCK 9: FAQ
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="home-block home-block--gray">
  <div class="home-wrap">
    <h2 class="section-title">FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details>
        <summary>How do you verify product purity?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Every batch undergoes independent third-party HPLC analysis. The Certificate of Analysis (COA) is included with every order and available for download on our website. We publish batch-specific purity data — never averages.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is your shipping and return policy?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Orders ship within 24 hours via express courier with cold-chain packaging where required. Domestic delivery takes 2-3 business days. If a product does not meet the stated purity specification, we offer a full refund within 90 days of purchase.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Are your products for human consumption?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">No. All products sold by GenScript are strictly for laboratory research and analytical purposes only. They are not intended for human or veterinary use. By purchasing, you certify that you are a qualified researcher affiliated with an accredited institution.</div>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do you ship internationally?</summary>
        <div class="faq-answer">Yes, we ship to over 40 countries. International orders typically arrive within 5-10 business days depending on customs clearance. All international shipments include proper documentation for customs purposes.</div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

